A boy has died after suffering a ‘medical episode’ at a house. He fell ill at around 12.30pm yesterday at a house in Salford and was taken to hospital. The boy, whose age has not yet been confirmed, died soon after arriving. Forensic officers were pictured outside the property on Firth Close after detectives launched an investigation into the death. A spokesperson said: ‘Police were called around 12.30pm on Sunday 13 March to Firth Close, Salford to a report of a child suffering from a medical episode. ‘The child – a boy – was taken to hospital but despite the best efforts of hospital staff sadly died a short while later. ‘Enquiries are ongoing.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.